Calculated Variable for Racial Demographics - Non-White and Racial Minority

Notes: 0= White/Caucasian selected; 1= Any/multiple racial minority categories selected. Calculated from demo_race___1-10 and demo_racial_identity.

ElementDescription: Calculated Variable for Latino/Latina/Latinx/Hispanic Ethnicity
Notes: 0= Did not endorse demo_race___5 (Latino, Latina, Latinx, or Hispanic); 1= Endorsed demo_race___5 (Latino, Latina, Latinx, or Hispanic)

ElementDescription: Dichotomous Variable for Special Education Services Use (from demo_school_accommod)
Notes: 0= Does not endorse receiving special education services; 1= Does endorse receiving special education services

ElementDescription: Calculated Variable for Highest Level of Educational Attainment
Notes: 1= Less than high school; 2= High school with modified diploma; 3= Typical high school diploma; 4= Some college; 5= Certificate/Associates degree; 6= Bachelors degree; 7= Graduate degree; Calculated from demo_highschool, demo_highschool_type, demo_college, demo_degree

ElementDescription: Calculated Variable for whether Major Life Events during the last 6 months are reported (from demo_live_events)
Notes: 0= No items checked on major life events checklist; 1= Any item(s) on major life events checklist selected

ElementDescription: Number of Major Life Events
4-Category Calculated Variable for Sexual Orientation (from demo_orientation)
Notes: 1= Straight/Heterosexual; 2= Gay/Lesbian; 3= Bi/Pansexual; 4= Other; Calculated from demo_orientation__ responses___1-10. Selection of higher numbers overrides selection of lower numbers

ElementDescription: 3-Category Calculated Variable for Gender Identity (from demo_gender, demo_sex_ab, demo_gender_as_ab)
